imdmCcTable.name: imdmCcTable
imdmCcTable.description: A table containing the call control parameters for each modem in the chassis.

imdmCcEntry.name: imdmCcEntry
imdmCcEntry.description: Call control parameters for an ISDN modem. These define the sequence of operation related to how a call is negotiated.

imdmCcIndex.name: imdmCcIndex
imdmCcIndex.description: The index which uniquely identifies the modem to which this entry is applicable. The value corresponds to the value of the index to the entity table in the chassis MIB that corresponds to the same modem.

imdmCcRateAdapV110.name: imdmCcRateAdapV110
imdmCcRateAdapV110.description: This object enables V110 rate adaption corresponds to S register S67 bit 0. Default = enable(2).

imdmCcFixedNtwkRate.name: imdmCcFixedNtwkRate
imdmCcFixedNtwkRate.description: This object sets the fixed network rate. This object correspond to S register S67 bit 1. Default = 1

imdmCcNetworkRate.name: imdmCcNetworkRate
imdmCcNetworkRate.description: This object sets the Network rate speed. This object corresponds to the modem S register S67 bit 2. Default = 1

imdmCcBcLinkDly.name: imdmCcBcLinkDly
imdmCcBcLinkDly.description: This object enable a 45 - 65 second link delay. This object corresponds to the S register S67 bit 4. Default = 1

imdmCcAnlgOvrDig.name: imdmCcAnlgOvrDig
imdmCcAnlgOvrDig.description: This object is used to set S register S68 bit 0 which, does not allow analog calls over digital data connection. Default = 1

imdmCcAsyncPPP.name: imdmCcAsyncPPP
imdmCcAsyncPPP.description: This object is used to disable/enable async PPP/ sync PPP conversion. This object corresponds to S register S68 bit 2. Default = enable(1).

imdmCcX75.name: imdmCcX75
imdmCcX75.description: This object is used to disable/enable X75. This object corresponds to S register S68 bit 3. Default = 1

imdmCcStarV2.name: imdmCcStarV2
imdmCcStarV2.description: This object is used to set the data mode of the modem and is equivalent to *V2 = x AT command. Default =1

imdmCcStarU1.name: imdmCcStarU1
imdmCcStarU1.description: This object is used to set the originate HDLC protocols of the modem and is equivalent to *U1 = x AT command. Default =2

imdmCcStarU2.name: imdmCcStarU2
imdmCcStarU2.description: This object is used to set the originate Non-HDLC protocols of the modem and is equivalent to *U2 = x AT command. Default =1

imdmCcStarU3.name: imdmCcStarU3
imdmCcStarU3.description: This object is used to set the originate Analog modem/fax data mode of the modem and is equivalent to *U3 = x AT command. Default =2

imdmCcV120.name: imdmCcV120
imdmCcV120.description: This Object is used to Enable/Disable V120. This Object corresponds to S register 68 bit 4 default=1

imdmCcFrameSize.name: imdmCcFrameSize
imdmCcFrameSize.description: This Object is used to set the Frame size for X75. Default = 2048

imdmCcWindowSize.name: imdmCcWindowSize
imdmCcWindowSize.description: This Object is used to set the Window Size of X75 default=2

imdmLiTable.name: imdmLiTable
imdmLiTable.description: A list of configurable Line Interface objects for a modem. The number of table entries is given by modem Number.

imdmLiEntry.name: imdmLiEntry
imdmLiEntry.description: Objects which define the line interface characteristics for a particular modem.

imdmLiIndex.name: imdmLiIndex
imdmLiIndex.description: Index into the Line Interface table. This index is the value from the chassis mib entity relation table that is applicable for a particular modem.

imdmLiConnTypeToCo.name: imdmLiConnTypeToCo
imdmLiConnTypeToCo.description: This object is used to set the type of switch your telephone company Cental Office is using. This object coressponds with the *M AT modem command.

imdmLiDN.name: imdmLiDN
imdmLiDN.description: This object is to set the Directory Number (DN) that is assigned by the telephone company. This object corresponds to the *P AT modem command.

imdmLiSPID.name: imdmLiSPID
imdmLiSPID.description: This object is to set the Service Profile ID (SPID) that is assigned by the telephone company. This object corresponds to the *S AT modem command.

imdmLiTermEndPointID.name: imdmLiTermEndPointID
imdmLiTermEndPointID.description: This object is to set the Terminal Endpoint ID (TEI) that is assigned by the telephone company. This object corresponds to the *T AT modem command.

imdmLiProtTypeSw.name: imdmLiProtTypeSw
imdmLiProtTypeSw.description: This object is to set the Switch Protocol that the telephone company uses. This object corresponds to the *W AT modem command.
